@page
@model IndexModel

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
    Layout = null;
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/fonts.css"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/pages/index.css"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/partialView/navBar.css"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/responsives/responsive.css"/>
</head>

<body>

<header>
    @await Html.PartialAsync("Shared/partialView/_NavBarPartial")
</header>

<main>
    <section class="backgroundHeaderIndex">
        <h1>StarColonies</h1>

        <div class="info">
            <p>Dive into the captivating universe of StarColonnies: The Age of Middleware, a galactic strategy and exploration
                game developed by Laudrikx Games.</p>
            <p>At the edge of a distant galaxy, you take on the role of a fearless colonist landing on an unknown planet. </p>
            <p>Joined by your team of specialists—engineers, medics, scientists, and soldiers—you will need to build, survive,
                explore, and dominate.</p>

            <div class="btn">
                <button class="buttonLoader" id="analyseBtn">
                    <span id="buttonText">Découvrez l'univers</span>
                    <div id="loaderBar" class="loader-bar hidden"></div>
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="hallOfFame">
        <h3>Hall of fame</h3>

        <div class="insideHallOfFame">
            <div class="leftColumnHallOfFame">
                <p>Welcome to the Hall of Fame, where only the top 10 colonies in the galaxy have earned their place among the stars.</p>
                <p>These are not mere squads—they are frontier legends, forged across countless star systems, hardened by the vacuum of
                    space, and united by a single mission: to thrive where others fall. Across deadly asteroid fields, rogue moons,
                    derelict outposts, and ancient alien ruins, these teams have braved the unknown—and emerged triumphant.</p>
                <p>Each of these colonies has completed missions that span the far reaches of the galaxy. They’ve faced cosmic storms,
                    battled swarms of bioengineered predators, hacked abandoned AI networks, and negotiated with entities beyond
                    comprehension. Through it all, they stood strong—thanks to tactical brilliance, adaptive strategy, and the sheer
                    will to survive.</p>
                <p>Their names are carved into history—not because of luck, but because of choices made under pressure, sacrifices accepted
                    without hesitation, and a relentless drive to protect and expand their influence among the stars.</p>
                <p>This Hall is more than a leaderboard—it's a monument to greatness, a source of inspiration for every aspiring explorer,
                    strategist, and commander in StarColonnies.</p>
                <p>The question remains: will your colony rise to claim its place among the galaxy’s finest?</p>
            </div>

            <div class="rightColumnHallOfFame">
                <hr/>

                <div class="topTenFame">
                    @foreach (var colony in Model.TopColonies)
                    {
                        <div class="oneFame">
                            <img src="~/img/upload/@colony.LogoPath" alt="teamLogo"/>
                            <h4>@colony.Name</h4>
                            <p>@colony.Strength</p>
                        </div>
                    }
                </div>

                <hr/>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="laudrikxSection">
        <img src="~/img/laudrikx_game.png" alt="laudrikx_game"/>
        <div class="laudrikxDescription">
            <h3>Laudrikx Games</h3>

            <p>At Laudrikx Games, we don’t just build games—we craft galaxies.</p>
            <p>Born from the minds of passionate storytellers, visionary designers, and veteran developers,
                Laudrikx Games is an independent studio dedicated to creating bold, immersive, and meaningful
                gaming experiences. We believe that video games are the most powerful form of interactive
                storytelling, and we strive to harness that power with every project we launch.</p>
            <p>With a strong focus on science fiction, tactical gameplay, and roleplaying depth, we aim to blur
                the lines between narrative and mechanics. Every pixel we place, every system we design, and
                every story we write is crafted to ignite the imagination and challenge the mind.</p>
            <p>Our latest venture, StarColonnies, is not just a game—it’s a dynamic and ever-expanding universe.
                In this futuristic saga, players take on the role of brave pioneers sent to explore, colonize,
                and survive in the most hostile corners of the galaxy. From assembling diverse teams of specialists,
                to unlocking lost technologies and confronting ancient alien threats, StarColonnies is a test of leadership,
                adaptability, and long-term strategy.</p>
            <p>Every decision matters. Every mission leaves a trace. And every player shapes a unique path through a living,
                evolving sci-fi sandbox.</p>
            <p>At Laudrikx Games, we don’t follow trends—we build worlds. And with StarColonnies, we invite you to become
                part of something bigger than yourself.</p>
            <p>Join us as we build the future—one colony at a time.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>

<script src="~/js/components/loader.js"></script>
<script src="~/js/components/nav_bar.js"></script>

<script>
    window.isAuthenticated = @User.Identity?.IsAuthenticated.ToString().ToLower();
</script>

</body>
</html>